 from eliot lanmola engr washington edu eliot subject horizontally opposed boxer engines was v four v six v eight v one two vx organization skulls r us lines four two nntp posting host lanmola engr washington edu in article bqueiser magnus acs ohio state edu brian j queiser writes there are two crank configurations for the flat four the most common one is probably the crank that is very similar to the i four crank which flat four engines have i four style cranks comparing those two engines the i four and the flat four have no first order shaking forces or rocking moments the i four has a second order shaking force while the flat four has a second order rocking moment the significant thing about the flat four s second order moment is that it can be easily balanced out by adding mass at the ends of the crank the i four however requires a counter rotating shaft with mass to balance out the second order forces i am nine nine nine nine sure that subaru and porsche use the boxer configuration and not the inline four crank that you analyzed and compared would you care to re evaluate the other case of a flat four i think that this configuration is perfectly balanced as far as primary secondary forces and couples are concerned i have an article in front of me that says so bottom line the biggest difference between the engines would probably be their intended use the flat four is easier to fit under low hoods and in rear compartments for mid or rear mounting the i four can be mounted transversely to reduce hood length read cab forward other than that there isn t much fanfare to the differences between them no matter what subaru ads say technology shared with porsche indeed the flat four is also shorter than an inline four so even if it is mounted longitudinally it will not take up lots of length and a longitudinal placement is easier for a four wheel drive drivetrain i think that subaru s ads hold water in practice their flat fours are noticeably smoother than inline four s and completely buzz free though some may not like its peculiar note but as alfa has shown a boxer four can produce a spine tingling scream that only the likes of recent hondas can approach eliot